Rush Limbaugh August 3, 2016 Full Podcast

Rush Hudson Limbaugh III is an American entertainer, radio talk show host, writer, and conservative political commentator. Since he was 16, Limbaugh has worked a series of disc jockey jobs. Wikipedia

What If the Public Doesn't See This Election the Way the Experts Do?

RUSH: What do you think of the premise that Hemmer put forth, that everything's so upside down that the manifestation of that is this. It looks to standard, ordinary, everyday political operatives like Trump is imploding. It looks like, "Oh, my God, it's a disaster! Oh, gee, this guy is just all over the map, doesn't have a message anymore."  But out there Trump is the vessel for the gazillions of people who are fed up with politics-as-usual and want no part of it.  And they don't care.  None of this traditional analysis of Trump imploding. Trump blowing it. Trump going off message.  That was the premise behind Hemmer's question.

Obama Sent Iran $400 Million Cash for Hostages -- and He Calls Trump Unfit?
August 03, 2016
